msgid "[[!meta title=\"Installing onto a USB stick\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Starting from version 0.11, Tails includes a custom USB installer to create "
"bootable USB sticks. The advantages of using Tails USB installer are that "
"you can:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
msgid "**use the extra space** left on the USB stick,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
msgid "**setup a persistent storage** to store some of your settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"But in order to use the USB installer, you need to start Tails from another "
"media than the USB you want to install. You can either:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
msgid "**[[Burn a Tails CD|download#index4h1]]** (recommended)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
msgid "**Use another Tails USB**, for example from a friend"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '  - '
msgid ""
"**[[Manually install Tails onto another USB stick|manual_usb_installation]]"
"**, if you can't use a CD"
msgstr ""
